debates.showAs: Health (Availability of General Practitioner Services) Bill 2025: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to make provision in relation to the availability of general practitioner medical and surgical services throughout the State, and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh socrú i ndáil le hinfhaighteacht seirbhísí liachta agus máinliachta lia-chleachtóirí ginearálta ar fud an Stáit, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: Health (Availability of General Practitioner Services) Bill 2025
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille Sláinte (Infhaighteacht Seirbhísí Lia-Chleachtóirí Ginearálta), 2025

debates.showAs: Disability (Personalised Budgets) Bill 2024: Second Stage
Disability (Personalised Budgets) Bill 2024: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to amend and extend the Disability Act 2005 and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do leasú agus do leathnú an Achta um Míchumas, 2005 agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.

debates.showAs: Workplace Relations (Exemplary Damages, Unfair Dismissals and Other Provisions) Bill 2024: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to enable the award of exemplary damages in certain circumstances by adjudication officers of the Workplace Relations Commission and by the Labour Court; to make certain non-disclosure agreements unenforceable as against employees who have not received independent advice; to make amendments to the Unfair Dismissals Act 1977 in order to give fuller effect to Directive (EU) 2019/1152 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 20 June 2019 on transparent and predictable working conditions in the European Union; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht dá chumasú d’oifigigh bhreithniúcháin don Choimisiún um Chaidreamh san Áit Oibre agus don Chúirt Oibreachais damáistí eiseamláireacha a dhámhachtain in imthosca áirithe; do dhéanamh comhaontuithe neamhnochta áirithe neamh-infhorfheidhmithe amhail i gcoinne fostaithe nach mbeidh comhairle neamhspleách faighte acu; do dhéanamh leasuithe ar an Acht um Dhífhostú Éagórach, 1977 d’fhonn éifeacht a thabhairt ar shlí níos iomláine do Threoir (AE) 2019/1152 ó Pharlaimint na hEorpa agus ón gComhairle an 20 Meitheamh 2019 maidir le dálaí oibre trédhearcacha agus intuartha san Aontas Eorpach; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: Workplace Relations (Exemplary Damages, Unfair Dismissals and Other Provisions) Bill 2024
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Chaidreamh san Áit Oibre (Damáistí Eiseamláireacha, Dífhostú Éagórach agus Forálacha Eile), 2024

debates.showAs: Disability (Miscellaneous Provisions) Bill 2023: Report and Final Stages

Disability (Miscellaneous Provisions) Bill 2023: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to amend the Disability Act 2005 and the Equal Status Act 2000 and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do leasú an Achta um Míchumas, 2005 agus an Achta um Stádas Comhionann, 2000 agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.

debates.showAs: National Minimum Wage (Inclusion of Apprentices) Bill 2023: Order for Second Stage
National Minimum Wage (Inclusion of Apprentices) Bill 2023: Second Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to provide for the inclusion of apprentices within the application of the National Minimum Wage Acts 2000 and 2015; for that purpose to amend the National Minimum Wage Act 2000; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh socrú maidir le printísigh a áireamh laistigh d’fheidhm na nAchtanna um Pá Íosta Náisiúnta, 2000 agus 2015; chun na críche sin, do leasú an Achta um Pá Íosta Náisiúnta, 2000; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: National Minimum Wage (Inclusion of Apprentices) Bill 2023
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Pá Íosta Náisiúnta (Printísigh a Áireamh), 2023

debates.showAs: Domestic Violence (Amendment) Bill 2023: Second Stage
Domestic Violence (Amendment) Bill 2023: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to amend and extend the Domestic Violence Act 2018 and, for that purpose, to provide protection in proceedings for the offence of coercive control against cross-examination in person by an accused person of a child witness or an adult witness who is the person in respect of whom the offence is alleged to have been committed and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do leasú agus do leathnú an Achta um Fhoréigean Baile, 2018 agus, chun na críche sin, do thabhairt cosaint in imeachtaí i leith an chiona arb éard é smachtú comhéigneach in aghaidh duine cúisithe do dhéanamh finné is leanbh nó finné is aosach, ar duine é nó í an finné a líomhnaítear go ndearnadh an cion ina leith, a chroscheistiú i bpearsa, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.

debates.showAs: Broadcasting (Gender, Cultural and Other Diversities) Bill 2022: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to secure in broadcasting a better reflection of the diversity of the people, for that purpose to amend the statutory duties of broadcasters, to provide for a quota of female composers or performers in relation to music content, and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht chun léiriú níos fearr ar éagsúlacht an phobail a áirithiú sa chraolachán, chun na críche sin, do leasú dualgais reachtúla craoltóirí, do dhéanamh socrú maidir le cuóta cumadóirí nó taibheoirí baineanna i ndáil le lánas ceoil, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: Broadcasting (Gender, Cultural and Other Diversities) Bill 2022
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille Craolacháin (Éagsúlachtaí Inscne, Cultúir agus Eile), 2022

debates.showAs: National Minimum Wage (Payment of Interns) Bill 2022: Second Stage
National Minimum Wage (Payment of Interns) Bill 2022: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to provide for the payment of the national minimum wage to certain persons doing work as interns or on work experience; for that purpose to amend the National Minimum Wage Act 2000; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh socrú maidir leis an bpá íosta náisiúnta a íoc le daoine áirithe a bheidh ag obair mar intéirnigh nó ag gabháil do thaithí oibre; chun na críche sin, do leasú an Achta um Pá Íosta Náisiúnta, 2000; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: National Minimum Wage (Payment of Interns) Bill 2022
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Pá Íosta Náisiúnta (Intéirnigh a Íoc), 2022

debates.showAs: Right to Flexible Work Bill 2022: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to provide employees with a right to flexible work, to require an employer to deal with a request for flexible work within a fixed period, to provide that an employer may refuse a request only on grounds of reasonable practicability, to require employers to maintain a policy on flexible work which can be inspected by employees and the Workplace Relations Commission, to provide for a right of appeal in certain circumstances against a refusal of flexible work, and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do thabhairt ceart chun oibre solúbtha d’fhostaithe, dá cheangal ar fhostóir déileáil le hiarraidh ar obair sholúbtha laistigh de thréimhse shocraithe, do dhéanamh socrú nach ceadmhach d’fhostóir iarraidh a dhiúltú ach amháin ar fhorais indéantachta réasúnaí, dá cheangal ar fhostóirí beartas maidir le hobair sholúbtha a chothabháil ar féidir le fostaithe agus leis an gCoimisiún um Chaidreamh san Áit Oibre iniúchadh a dhéanamh air, do dhéanamh socrú maidir le ceart achomhairc in imthosca áirithe i gcoinne obair sholúbtha a dhiúltú, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um an gCeart chun Oibre Solúbtha, 2022

debates.showAs: Social Welfare (Surviving Cohabitant’s Pension) Bill 2021: Second Stage
Social Welfare (Surviving Cohabitant’s Pension) Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to amend the Social Welfare Consolidation Act 2005 to entitle surviving cohabitants to a contributory pension; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do leasú an Achta Comhdhlúite Leasa Shóisialaigh, 2005 chun teideal chun pinsin ranníocaigh a thabhairt do chomhchónaitheoirí marthanacha; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille Leasa Shóisialaigh (Pinsean Comhchónaitheora Mharthanaigh), 2021

debates.showAs: Safe Access to Termination of Pregnancy Services Bill 2021: Report and Final Stages

Safe Access to Termination of Pregnancy Services Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to protect the free and unencumbered access to facilities providing legal termination of pregnancy services; protect individuals providing or facilitating legal termination of pregnancy services from harassment; and to provide for matters connected therewith.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht chun rochtain gan bhac gan chonstaic ar shaoráidí a sholáthraíonn seirbhísí foirceanta toirchis dlíthiúla a chosaint; chun daoine a sholáthraíonn nó a éascaíonn seirbhísí foirceanta toirchis dlíthiúla a chosaint ar chiapadh; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe a bhaineann leis an méid sin.
bill.shortTitleEn: Safe Access to Termination of Pregnancy Services Bill 2021
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Rochtain Shábháilte ar Sheirbhísí Foirceanta Toirchis, 2021

debates.showAs: Protection of Employment (Platform Workers and Bogus Self-Employment) Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to declare the relationship between employer and employee to be a status relationship, to declare the question whether an individual is an employee or is self-employed to be a question of law to be independently determined, to provide that the description given by the parties shall not be conclusive in determining the true status of an employment relationship, to provide for a presumption in favour of employee status in certain cases, to clarify the employment status of individuals who undertake personally to execute work or service for third parties, to take certain measures to counter the misrepresentation of the status of employees, to amend the Terms of Employment (Information) Act 1994, and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht dá dhearbhú gur caidreamh stádais an caidreamh idir fostóir agus fostaí, dá dhearbhú gur ceist dlí í an cheist i dtaobh an fostaí nó an duine féinfhostaithe pearsa aonair, ar ceist dlí í a bheidh le cinneadh go neamhspleách, do dhéanamh socrú nach tuairisc chríochnaitheach an tuairisc a thabharfaidh na páirtithe le linn stádas fírinneach caidrimh fostaíochta a chinneadh, do dhéanamh socrú maidir le toimhde i bhfabhar stádas fostaí i gcásanna áirithe, do shoiléiriú stádas fostaíochta pearsana aonair a ghabhfaidh orthu féin obair nó seirbhís a chur i gcrích go pearsanta do thríú páirtithe, do dhéanamh bearta áirithe chun cur i gcoinne stádas fostaithe a mhífhaisnéisiú, do leasú an Achta um Théarmaí Fostaíochta (Faisnéis), 1994, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleEn: Protection of Employment (Platform Workers and Bogus Self-Employment) Bill 2021
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Chaomhnú Fostaíochta (Oibrithe Ardáin agus Féinfhostaíocht Bhréagach), 2021

debates.showAs: Gambling (Prohibition of Advertising) Bill 2021: Second Stage
Gambling (Prohibition of Advertising) Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to regulate in the public interest advertising and sponsorship of gambling; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh rialáil, ar mhaithe le leas an phobail, ar fhógraíocht agus urraíocht ar chearrbhachas; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.
bill.shortTitleGa: An Bille um Chearrbhachas (Fógraíocht a Thoirmeasc), 2021

Organisation of Working Time (Reproductive Health Related Leave) Bill 2021: Committee Stage
Organisation of Working Time (Reproductive Health Related Leave) Bill 2021: Second Stage
Organisation of Working Time (Reproductive Health Related Leave) Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to provide for a period of paid leave consequent upon miscarriage or for the purposes of availing of reproductive healthcare; for that purpose to amend the Organisation of Working Time Act 1997; to extend the protection against unfair dismissals conferred by the Unfair Dismissals Acts 1977 to 2015; to provide for the consequential amendment of certain other Acts; and to provide for related matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh socrú maidir le tréimhse saoire le pá de dhroim breith anabaí nó chun leas a bhaint as cúram sláinte atáirgthe; chun na críche sin, do leasú an Achta um Eagrú Ama Oibre, 1997; do leathnú na cosanta ar dhífhostú éagórach a thugtar leis na hAchtanna um Dhífhostú Éagórach, 1977 go 2015; do dhéanamh socrú maidir le leasú iarmhartach a dhéanamh ar Achtanna áirithe eile; agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe gaolmhara.

debates.showAs: Adoption (Information and Tracing) Bill 2021: First Stage

bill.longTitleEn: Bill entitled an Act to provide for improved information and tracing for adopted persons in relation to their adoption, for that purpose to amend the Adoption Act 2010 so as to provide for access by adult adopted persons to the index maintained by an tArd-Chláraitheoir of connections between entries in the Adopted Children Register and the register of births, and to provide for connected matters.
bill.longTitleGa: Bille dá ngairtear Acht do dhéanamh socrú maidir le faisnéis agus rianú feabhsaithe do dhaoine uchtaithe i ndáil lena n-uchtáil, chun na críche sin do leasú an Achta Uchtála, 2010 d’fhonn socrú a dhéanamh maidir le rochtain a bheith ag daoine uchtaithe fásta ar an treoir, arna cothabháil ag an Ard-Chláraitheoir, de cheangail idir iontrálacha sa Chlár d’Uchtleanaí agus i gclár na mbreitheanna, agus do dhéanamh socrú i dtaobh nithe comhghaolmhara.

Planning and Development (Amendment) Bill 2021: First Stage
